/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/vasseur-pressure/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT-SUMMARY.md:18:- **[CHECKED]:** 5 claims (CZ theory, drift-diffusion closure, Bogovskii constants against literature)
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/vasseur-pressure/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT-SUMMARY.md:26:2. **De Giorgi recursion (structural):** The pressure decomposes into local and far-field parts. The local part closes the recursion (δ_local = 3/5 > 0). The far-field part has a FIXED CONSTANT coefficient that makes the U_k exponent sublinear (σ_far < 1). Only ε-regularity (smallness assumption) controls the constant.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/vasseur-pressure/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT-SUMMARY.md:28:The measure exponent 1/10 in the local pressure estimate is remarkably β-independent — a structural feature worth understanding deeper.
