/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/vasseur-pressure/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT.md:462:- The far-field coefficient is controlled only in the ε-regularity setting
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/vasseur-pressure/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT.md:464:The β = 4/3 is the **optimal subcritical exponent from the energy class in the time direction:** u ∈ L^{8/3}_t L^4_x → p ∈ L^{4/3}_t L^2_x. It represents the best strong-type pressure integrability achievable below the critical threshold.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/vasseur-pressure/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT.md:470:1. **Improving the far-field pressure control:** The local pressure already closes the recursion (δ_local = 3/5 > 0). The entire difficulty is in the far-field. Any technique that bounds ||p_far||_{L^∞(Q_k)} in terms of U_k (rather than a fixed constant) would close the gap.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/vasseur-pressure/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT.md:472:2. **Avoiding pressure localization entirely:** The Bogovskii corrector fails because localization costs 2^{2k}. Methods that work with the GLOBAL pressure (not localized to Q_k) avoid this cost.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/vasseur-pressure/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT.md:474:3. **Exploiting the 1/10 universality:** The measure exponent 1/10 in the local pressure estimate is independent of β. This suggests a deeper structural reason why the local contribution is well-behaved. Understanding this structure might reveal how to handle the far-field.
