/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/winning-chain.md:29:- It is more genuinely beyond-De-Giorgi than the architecture-fixed reformulation test.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/judgments/chain-01.md:5:The attacker is mostly right, but not all the way. The original chain is a credible branch if it is treated as a bounded obstruction test for exact-reformulation hopes inside one inherited estimate architecture. It is not credible as a primary discovery program for the mission's live beyond-De-Giorgi mechanism.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/judgments/chain-01.md:7:Its real strengths should be preserved: it asks for estimate-level gains, rejects identity-level cosmetics, and is willing to end with a negative memo. Its real weaknesses also need repair: it does not fix the architecture sharply enough, leaves the Tao screen too verbal, treats geometry/tensor effects too much as contamination, and makes the negative endpoint easier to earn than the positive one.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/judgments/chain-01.md:15:This is a fair warning, but not a full invalidation. The original chain does assume that any useful exact-rewrite signal should appear as an improvement on one localized bottleneck term in an inherited proof architecture. That can miss mechanisms that only emerge after changing the propagated quantity or contradiction setup.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/judgments/chain-01.md:17:Still, that limitation is acceptable if the branch is labeled honestly. A cleanup test of the "maybe an exact rewrite helps inside the old architecture" loophole is worth running. What is not acceptable is advertising that cleanup branch as a broad search for the mission's hidden mechanism.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/judgments/chain-01.md:41:The refined chain should classify those effects early, not treat them as an afterthought, and only close negatively when the surviving effect is geometry-only or architecture-changing with no remainder in the fixed setup.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/judgments/chain-01.md:49:That is acceptable only if the final negative claim is correspondingly narrow: a bounded obstruction result on a specified architecture and candidate family, not a verdict on reformulation as a strategy in general.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/judgments/chain-01.md:79:This lands. A "concrete proposition" is not enough unless the chain says what proof architecture it feeds and what quantitative benchmark counts as a material improvement. The final claim also has to stay narrow: at best this branch can certify that a specified reformulation family fails to produce a Tao-relevant gain within one fixed architecture.
