/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/judgments/chain-01.md:92:8. Narrow the negative endpoint to exactly the tested architecture and candidate family.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:5:The attacker is mostly right. The original chain is disciplined and worth keeping, but only as a narrowly scoped obstruction branch, not as a broad discovery program for the mission's beyond-De-Giorgi mechanism. Its main strengths are real: it asks for estimate-level gains, it front-loads killing cosmetic rewrites, and it is willing to end negatively. Its main weaknesses are also real: it leaves the target architecture under-specified, states the Tao screen too loosely, treats geometry too much as contamination, and makes the negative endpoint easier to earn than the positive one.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:7:The correct refinement is to fix one inherited estimate architecture at the start, define the gain in one bookkeeping currency, require an explicit Tao discriminator, and treat this branch as a bounded test of whether exact NS reformulations or one tightly specified paired auxiliary quantity can beat the named bottleneck. If not, the obstruction memo is the intended success case.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:15:This critique lands, but only partly. It is true that the original chain assumes success should register as an improvement on a localized or truncated bottleneck term inside an inherited proof architecture. That risks missing mechanisms that only become visible after changing the propagated object or contradiction setup.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:17:But this does not make the branch illegitimate. A focused cleanup test of the "maybe an exact rewrite helps inside the current architecture" loophole is still worthwhile. The fix is not to turn this branch into a global discovery program. The fix is to state honestly that it is an obstruction/cleanup branch and to allow at most one tightly specified auxiliary-quantity variant so the negative result is not hard-coded from the start.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:41:So the refinement must make the endpoint explicit: a bounded obstruction statement on a specified architecture and candidate family counts as success, but nothing broader is earned.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:55:This critique lands cleanly. The chain has to choose one inherited architecture at the start, name the exact bad term inside it, and define one bookkeeping notion of gain that all candidates are judged against. Otherwise the shortlist is driven too much by taste and the candidates are not truly comparable.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:85:The negative endpoint also has to be tightly phrased. At best, this branch can rule out a specified family of exact reformulations relative to one fixed architecture, not reformulation gains in general.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:92:2. Fix one inherited proof architecture and one named bad term at the opening step.
