+# Exploration 001 Report
+
+## Goal
+
+Choose exactly one inherited architecture and exactly one named bad term for
+`step-005` of `Fixed-Protocol Obstruction Audit for Exact NS Reformulations`.
+
+Required candidate architectures:
+
+- `De Giorgi truncation`
+- `local-energy flux/localization`
+- `vorticity stretching localization`
+
+## Method
+
+- Read the local mission and chain record named in the task.
+- Extract already-established negatives that constrain the choice.
+- Compare the three candidate architectures against those constraints.
+- Fix one auditable bad term inside the selected architecture.
+
+## Running Findings Log
+
+### Initial setup
+
+- [VERIFIED] Report skeleton created before source review.
+
+### Source-grounded constraints
+
+- [VERIFIED] `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/MISSION.md` fixes two mission negatives
+  that sharply constrain Step 5 architecture choice:
+  - the De Giorgi-Vasseur framework is already exhausted, with `beta = 4/3`
+    treated as the sharp barrier inside that architecture;
+  - the earlier pressure mission killed the pressure-localization/H^1 rescue
+    route and identified the far-field pressure obstruction as coefficient-side.
+- [VERIFIED] `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/planner.md`
+  explicitly says this run will not spend budget on De Giorgi tuning, stronger
+  pressure exponents, or renamed `H^1/BMO` variants.
+- [VERIFIED] `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/steps/step-001/RESULTS.md` closes the
+  harmonic-tail pressure branch negatively:
+  the live far-field problem is the coefficient for the surviving pairing, and
+  generic harmonic regularity or algebraic repackaging does not shrink it in a
+  Tao-relevant way.
+- [VERIFIED] `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/steps/step-004/RESULTS.md` kills the
+  geometry/stretched-vorticity branch on its fixed Eulerian package:
+  no candidate cleared the dynamic plausibility screen, and continuation would
+  be blind momentum rather than an earned next step.
+- [VERIFIED] `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/CHAIN.md`,
+  `planning-runs/run-003/selected/chain-01.md`,
+  `planning-runs/run-003/refined/chain-01.md`, and
+  `planning-runs/run-003/judgments/chain-01.md` all frame the present chain as
+  a bounded estimate-level audit of exact rewrites inside one fixed inherited
+  local architecture.
+
+### Candidate architecture comparison
+
+#### 1. `De Giorgi truncation`
+
+- [VERIFIED] Local support exists for this as an inherited architecture:
+  `missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/vasseur-2007-proof-architecture.md`
+  gives the full De Giorgi localization stack.
+- [VERIFIED] The same local source record already identifies its bottleneck:
+  Vasseur's local pressure term bottoms out at exponent `4/3`, while the
+  mission and planner record treat that wall as exhausted rather than as a live
+  tuning target.
+- [VERIFIED] `missions/vasseur-pressure/steps/step-002/RESULTS.md` records
+  three independent failures for exploiting pressure `H^1` structure inside the
+  De Giorgi recursion, with the common obstruction named as the `W^{1,3}` wall.
+- [VERIFIED] `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/steps/step-001/RESULTS.md` separately
+  kills the remaining far-field pressure-tail loophole.
+- [INFERRED] Therefore a Step-5 choice of `De Giorgi truncation` would not
+  create a fresh fixed-protocol audit. It would mainly reopen already-closed
+  pressure-side negatives under a different label.
+- [INFERRED] Rival status:
+  `already exhausted / strongly prefigured by prior negatives`.
+
+#### 2. `vorticity stretching localization`
+
+- [VERIFIED] Local support exists for this as an inherited architecture in the
+  geometry branch record:
+  `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/steps/step-002/RESULTS.md`,
+  `steps/step-003/RESULTS.md`, and `steps/step-004/RESULTS.md`.
+- [VERIFIED] The narrowed live object on that branch was
+  `direction coherence + tube persistence`, not a pure exact-rewrite family.
+- [VERIFIED] `steps/step-004/RESULTS.md` then kills the branch on the fixed
+  neutral Eulerian package because every candidate is dynamically weak or
+  static-only.
+- [VERIFIED] `MISSION.md` also records that exact Beltrami cancellation is
+  fragile and that even the vorticity formulation still lands at the same
+  `4/3` barrier; the quadratic obstruction is not cured merely by passing to
+  vorticity variables.
+- [VERIFIED] `steps/step-005/REASONING.md` states the same strategic lesson:
+  the natural rewrite shortlist (`Lamb-vector`, projected form, vorticity
+  transport) mismatches the stretching target and risks reopening the killed
+  geometry branch.
+- [INFERRED] Therefore `vorticity stretching localization` is the wrong fixed
+  architecture for an exact-rewrite audit here. On the present record it is
+  either already killed on its honest package or it asks for a geometry reboot,
+  which would be a different branch.
+- [INFERRED] Rival status:
+  `too mismatched to the natural rewrite shortlist / already branch-killed on
+  the local package`.
+
+#### 3. `local-energy flux/localization`
+
+- [VERIFIED] `missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/ckn-1982-proof-architecture.md`
+  puts the local energy inequality at the center of the inherited localized
+  balance:
+  `2 ∬ |∇u|^2 φ <= ∬ |u|^2 (∂_t φ + Δφ) + ∬ (|u|^2 + 2p) u · ∇φ`.
+- [VERIFIED] That same source isolates the two cutoff-gradient pieces of the
+  local-energy flux:
+  - transport: `∬ |u|^2 u · ∇φ`
+  - pressure transport: `2 ∬ p u · ∇φ`.
+- [VERIFIED] `planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-01.md` explicitly names a
+  `local-energy flux term` as one of the legitimate architecture candidates
+  that must be fixed sharply at Step 1 rather than left vague.
+- [VERIFIED] `steps/step-005/REASONING.md` and the receptionist note in
+  `runtime/results/codex-patlas-standalone-20260331T124016Z-receptionist-89481.md`
+  both converge on the same recommendation:
+  ground the audit in the inherited local-energy / localized-balance
+  architecture and target the localized quadratic flux-type term after cutoff
+  bookkeeping.
+- [INFERRED] This is the best-supported architecture because it stays inside a
+  genuine inherited estimate mechanism, does not require reopening the killed
+  far-field pressure coefficient branch, and does not depend on the killed
+  geometry package.
+- [INFERRED] Winning status:
+  `best supported for a fixed-protocol exact-rewrite audit`.
+
+### Final architecture choice
+
+- [VERIFIED] Chosen inherited architecture:
+  `local-energy flux/localization`.
+
+### Final bad-term choice
+
+- [PROPOSED] Freeze the unique audit target as the **localized cutoff-flux
+  bundle in the local energy inequality**
+
+  `I_flux[φ;u,p] := ∬_{Q_r} (|u|^2 + 2p) u · ∇φ`.
+
+- [INFERRED] This should count as one named bad term, not as a menu of terms.
+  Later steps may decompose it internally into transport and pressure pieces,
+  but a claimed gain only counts if it improves the bound on this same bundle
+  after full localization bookkeeping.
+- [INFERRED] The bundle, rather than the isolated pressure subterm
+  `2 ∬ p u · ∇φ`, is the right frozen target because:
+  - choosing only the pressure piece would slide back toward the already-killed
+    far-field pressure branch;
+  - choosing only the cubic transport piece would let later rewrites move loss
+    into pressure and claim cosmetic progress;
+  - exact rewrites of the NS nonlinearity naturally redistribute mass between
+    convective and pressure-looking pieces, so the whole cutoff-flux bundle is
+    the stable estimate-level object.
+
+### Why this is not a disguised rerun
+
+#### Not the killed far-field pressure branch
+
+- [VERIFIED] `steps/step-001/RESULTS.md` fixed the dead pressure target as the
+  far-field pairing coefficient `I_p^far` and its effective constant
+  `C_far,eff(k)`.
+- [INFERRED] The chosen bad term is different:
+  it is the one-cylinder local-energy cutoff-flux bundle itself, not a
+  harmonic-tail coefficient problem and not a moment problem for affine or
+  higher harmonic pressure modes.
+- [INFERRED] Later success here would have to improve the localized balance
+  before any far-field coefficient diagnosis, rather than shrinking the already
+  isolated `C_far`.
+
+#### Not the killed geometry branch
+
+- [VERIFIED] `steps/step-004/RESULTS.md` kills the geometry route on the fixed
+  Eulerian intense-set package and says any honest revisit must be an openly new
+  branch with an openly changed package.
+- [INFERRED] The chosen architecture does not rely on
+  `direction coherence + tube persistence`, on a vorticity thresholded intense
+  set, or on a kernel-level representation of `S omega . omega`.
+- [INFERRED] The localization object is the standard parabolic cutoff `φ` from
+  the local-energy inequality, not a tube-adapted or geometry-adapted package.
+
+#### Not a rerun of vorticity / Beltrami fragility
+
+- [VERIFIED] `MISSION.md` already records that exact Beltrami kills the
+  Lamb-vector / pressure-side loss only in an extremely fragile regime, and the
+  vorticity formulation itself does not beat the `4/3` obstruction.
+- [INFERRED] By freezing `I_flux[φ;u,p]` as the target, later steps prevent
+  themselves from counting regime-specific alignment or stretching-language
+  effects as success unless those effects produce a real gain on the same local
+  cutoff-flux bundle under generic bookkeeping.
+
+### What later success would mean in this setup
+
+- [PROPOSED] Later success means:
+  under one fixed suitable-weak-solution/local-energy package and one frozen
+  parabolic cutoff protocol, an exact rewrite or one same-target hybrid route
+  yields a strictly better estimate for `I_flux[φ;u,p]` after paying all
+  cutoff, projection, and commutator losses.
+- [INFERRED] In this architecture, "better" should be read in the local record's
+  preferred currency as a **closure improvement in the same localized balance**,
+  not as a prettier identity, a geometry-only artifact, or a transfer of the
+  same loss into another branch.
+- [INFERRED] If no rewrite changes the effective local-energy balance on
+  `I_flux[φ;u,p]`, the correct later endpoint is a bounded obstruction memo on
+  exact reformulations in this architecture.
+
+## Dead Ends / Failed Attempts
+
+- [VERIFIED] No local source support was found for reopening
+  `De Giorgi truncation` without re-entering already-settled pressure-side
+  negatives.
+- [VERIFIED] No local source support was found for promoting
+  `vorticity stretching localization` without undoing the explicit Step-4 kill
+  of the geometry branch.
+
+## Provisional Conclusion
+
+- [VERIFIED] Final architecture:
+  `local-energy flux/localization`.
+- [PROPOSED] Final named bad term:
+  the localized cutoff-flux bundle
+  `I_flux[φ;u,p] = ∬ (|u|^2 + 2p) u · ∇φ`.
+- [INFERRED] This is the narrowest source-supported choice that is concrete
+  enough for later estimate testing and does not quietly collapse into a
+  pressure rerun or geometry rerun.

